Array Initialization:

Suppose we initialize the array with size 10: arr = [ , , , , , , , , , ].

top1 = -1 (Stack 1 is empty).

top2 = 10 (Stack 2 is empty).

Push Elements:

push1(5) â†’ top1 = 0, array becomes: [5, , , , , , , , , ].

push1(10) â†’ top1 = 1, array becomes: [5, 10, , , , , , , , ].

push2(20) â†’ top2 = 9, array becomes: [5, 10, , , , , , , , 20].

push2(30) â†’ top2 = 8, array becomes: [5, 10, , , , , , , 30, 20].

Pop Elements:

pop1() â†’ top1 = 0, returns 10, array becomes: [5, , , , , , , , 30, 20].

pop1() â†’ top1 = -1, returns 5, array becomes: [ , , , , , , , , 30, 20].

pop2() â†’ top2 = 9, returns 30, array becomes: [ , , , , , , , , , 20].

pop2() â†’ top2 = 10, returns 20, array becomes: [ , , , , , , , , , ].

